@flexiarg coordination/intent-to-mission-binding
@title Intent to Mission Binding (G5)
@keywords mission, intent, binding, scope, success-criteria
@audience coordination maintainers, futon3b builders
@tone formal-analytic
@references [futon-theory/agent-contract futon-theory/stop-the-line]
@theory-grounding [I5(Model-adequacy) A3(Evidence-driven)]

! conclusion:
  If you want progress claims to be comparable across sessions, bind each task to an explicit mission reference and success criteria before authorization or execution.

  + context: Intent strings are not enough; the system needs mission-scoped obligations.
  + IF:
    you want the same "kind of work" to be evaluated consistently over time

  + HOWEVER:
    free-form intent without mission binding makes evidence drift and prevents traceability to devmaps

  + THEN:
    require `:task/mission-ref` and `:task/success-criteria` and verify mission is active at G5

  + BECAUSE:
    mission binding is the only stable anchor that makes later PSR/PUR/PAR meaningful

